## Core principle

Ship beautiful AND accessible. These are not trade-offs — they are both mandatory.

## Accessibility (WCAG 2.2 Level AA baseline)

### Perceivable
- Every `<img>` has `alt` text. Decorative images get `alt=""`.
- Color contrast: 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text (18px+ bold or 24px+ regular).
- UI components: 3:1 contrast against their background.
- Never convey meaning with color alone — add icons, text, or patterns.
- Pages must work at 200% browser zoom without horizontal scroll.

### Operable
- All interactive elements reachable and usable via keyboard alone.
- Visible focus indicators on every focusable element. Never `outline: none` without a replacement.
- Focus indicators: minimum 2px, contrasting color.
- Click/tap targets: minimum 44x44 CSS pixels (48x48 preferred for mobile).
- Drag-and-drop must have a click/keyboard alternative.
- No keyboard traps — user can always Tab away.

### Understandable
- Heading hierarchy: H1 → H2 → H3. Never skip levels.
- Every form field has a visible `<label>` programmatically linked (`htmlFor` / `id`).
- Error messages identify the field and describe the problem in text — not just a red border.
- Consistent navigation: same position and order across pages.
- `lang` attribute set on `<html>`.

### Robust
- Use semantic HTML first: `<button>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<article>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`.
- Custom components: expose `role`, `aria-label`, `aria-expanded`, `aria-live` as needed.
- Dynamic content updates: use `aria-live="polite"` for status messages, `"assertive"` for errors.
- Modals: trap focus inside, return focus to trigger on close.

## Visual design defaults

### Layout
- Mobile-first: design for 320px then scale up.
- Use a responsive grid system (CSS Grid or Flexbox).
- Max content width: 65-75 characters per line for readability.
- Consistent spacing scale (4px base: 4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32, 48, 64).

### Typography
- System font stack or one web font max (two weights: regular + bold).
- Base font size: 16px minimum. Never below 14px for body text.
- Line height: 1.5 for body, 1.2-1.3 for headings.
- Limit to 3-4 font sizes per page (use a type scale).

### Color
- Define a palette: 1 primary, 1 secondary, 1 accent, neutrals (gray scale), semantic (success/warning/error/info).
- Use CSS custom properties / design tokens — never hardcode hex values inline.
- Dark mode: if supported, provide proper contrast in both themes.
- Test with a color blindness simulator before shipping.

### Components
- Buttons: clear hierarchy — primary (filled), secondary (outlined), tertiary (text/ghost).
- Forms: labels above inputs, clear placeholder text (not as labels), inline validation.
- Cards: consistent padding, clear visual boundary, scannable content.
- Tables: sticky header, zebra stripes or hover highlight for long tables, responsive overflow.
- Loading: skeleton screens over spinners. Show progress for operations > 2 seconds.
- Empty states: helpful message + call to action — never a blank page.
- Toast/notification: auto-dismiss after 5s, closable, accessible with `role="status"`.

### Interaction
- Hover states on all clickable elements.
- Transitions: 150-300ms ease. No animation over 500ms unless purposeful.
- Disable buttons during async operations to prevent double-submit.
- Optimistic UI for fast-feeling interactions (update UI, then confirm with server).

## Responsive breakpoints (suggested)

| Name | Min width | Typical device |
|------|-----------|---------------|
| xs | 0 | Small phone |
| sm | 640px | Large phone |
| md | 768px | Tablet |
| lg | 1024px | Laptop |
| xl | 1280px | Desktop |
| 2xl | 1536px | Large monitor |

Test at: 320px, 768px, 1024px, 1440px minimum.

## Common anti-patterns — reject these

| Anti-pattern | Why it's bad | Do this instead |
|---|---|---|
| Placeholder-only labels | Disappear on focus, fail accessibility | Use visible `<label>` above input |
| `div` with `onClick` instead of `<button>` | Not keyboard accessible, no role | Use `<button>` or `<a>` |
| `outline: none` globally | Removes keyboard focus indicator | Replace with visible custom focus ring |
| Fixed pixel fonts | Break zoom and responsive scaling | Use rem/em units |
| Text in images | Can't be read by screen readers, not searchable | Use HTML text with CSS styling |
| Auto-playing media | Distracting, accessibility violation | Let user initiate playback |
| Infinite scroll without alternative | Inaccessible, can't reach footer | Add "Load more" or pagination option |
| Color-only error states | Invisible to color-blind users | Add icon + text alongside color |
| Tiny tap targets | Frustrating on mobile, accessibility failure | Minimum 44x44px |
| No loading feedback | User doesn't know if action worked | Skeleton, spinner, or progress bar |

## Checklist before merging any UI change

- [ ] Keyboard-navigable: Tab through the entire flow without a mouse
- [ ] Focus indicators visible on every interactive element
- [ ] All images have appropriate alt text
- [ ] Color contrast passes (use browser DevTools or axe)
- [ ] Form fields have visible, linked labels
- [ ] Error messages are descriptive and in text
- [ ] Responsive: tested at 320px, 768px, 1440px
- [ ] No layout-breaking horizontal scroll at 200% zoom
- [ ] Semantic HTML used (no div soup)
- [ ] Loading and empty states handled
- [ ] Transitions are smooth (150-300ms)
- [ ] Design tokens / CSS variables used — no hardcoded colors

## When NOT to enforce strictly

- Internal admin tools: accessibility still matters but pixel-perfect polish can be lighter.
- Prototype / spike: skip polish but keep semantic HTML and keyboard access.
- Email templates: limited CSS support — do the best you can within constraints.
